title: Dalberg logo, spiky serif
content:
I realize this could be a custom font but if anyone can ID it that would be great, thanks!

| Attachment | Size |
| --- | --- |
| [D Capital Logo - Color.png](http://web.archive.org/web/20150313022552/http:/typophile.com/files/D%20Capital%20Logo%20-%20Color.png) | 60.87 KB |
author: pattyfab

comments.content:
All text must be **[Swift](http://web.archive.org/web/20150313022552/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=Linotype&ffam=Swift%20-%20Regular&fid=55ef7f5bc1721a36aaff8f93e40240f0&fsize=60&text=D.Capita%20Investing%20for%20Impact&wrap=2)** by Gerard Unger [1989] except of the terminating "L" which looks like **[Highlander](http://web.archive.org/web/20150313022552/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=Dafont-1&ffam=Highlander%20-%20Regular&fid=a0f29ffff1acd895bb8dd7f81d852f36&fsize=60&text=L&fit=1)** free font by beccaelizabeth  
The logo looks like is was made by the investors themselves [what a terrible taste!]
Thank you!!!! The L is customized I think.
